ix) NGINX :- 
NGINX is open source software that powers web servers and enables reverse proxying, caching, load balancing, and media streaming. 
It was originally designed as a web server with high performance and reliability.

In one line:
ğŸ‘‰ It receives requests from users and forwards them to your application efficiently.

ğŸ§  Simple Example: Ticket Counter
Without NGINX  =======>

Everyone directly crowds your Spring Boot app.
Your app = 1 ticket counter â†’ gets overloaded â†’ slow or crashes.

With NGINX  ==============>

NGINX = smart security guard who:

Organizes the line
Sends people one by one
Blocks bad requests
Caches repeated answers
Handles static files (images, JS, CSS)
Distributes load to multiple app instances
Your app now handles only the real work.

â­ Key Benefits in 1 Line Each
âœ” 1. Caching
If 100 users ask the same thing â†’ NGINX replies instantly from cache â†’ your app handles only 1 request instead of 100.

âœ” 2. Load balancing
NGINX can send requests to multiple Spring Boot instances â†’ more users supported.

âœ” 3. Security
Blocks strange, slow, or malicious requests before they hit your Spring app.

âœ” 4. Static files
NGINX serves CSS/JS/images 10x faster than Spring Boot.

âœ” 5. Reverse Proxy
Makes your app hide behind port 80 â†’ user-friendly URL:


http://yourserver

instead of:
http://yourserver:8080

